        <simplesect>
            <title>Detailed Description</title>

<para>The offset is a 32 bit value, split in two parts. It represents the address of the entry point of the ISR. The selector is a 16 bit value and must point to a valid CS descriptor in your GDT. The type_attr is specified here: 7 0 +&#8212;+&#8212;+&#8212;+&#8212;+&#8212;+&#8212;+&#8212;+&#8212;+ | P | DPL | S | GateType | +&#8212;+&#8212;+&#8212;+&#8212;+&#8212;+&#8212;+&#8212;+&#8212;+ </para>
